\
\'95 Total budget\
\
\'95 Capital\
\
\'95 Recurrent\
\
\'95 Debt (where applicable)\
\
This becomes one of the primary constitutional objects on every page.\
\
---\
\
# Timeline\
\
The timeline is not news.\
\
The timeline is not a social feed.\
\
The timeline is a constitutional activity stream.\
\
Every item is generated from admitted truth.\
\
Examples:\
\
Budget admitted.\
\
Chairman changed.\
\
Project updated.\
\
Court judgment admitted.\
\
Audit report admitted.\
\
FOI response admitted.\
\
Election result admitted.\
\
Procurement admitted.\
\
No editorial writing should exist.\
\
Everything derives from constitutional truth.\
\
---\
\
# Constitutional Rendering\
\
Every timeline item is a projection of:\
\
Truth Product\
\
\uc0\u8595 \
\
Projection Rule\
\
\uc0\u8595 \
\
Timeline Card\
\
No manual timeline management should exist.\
\
---\
\
# Missing Constitutional Information\
\
The operating system should gracefully represent missing information.\
\
Examples:\
\
No budget admitted.\
\
No official photograph.\
\
No current representative.\
\
No audit report.\
\
These should be presented using beautiful constitutional placeholder artwork rather than empty UI.\
\
Missing information is treated as an incomplete public record.\
\
Not an application error.\
\
---\
\
# Projection Philosophy\
\
The Citizen application does not own constitutional truth.\
\
It projects constitutional truth.\
\
Every section is a projection.\
\
Every card is a projection.\
\
Every relationship is a projection.\
\
Every timeline event is a projection.\
\
Applications never manufacture constitutional information.\
\
---\
\
# Stable Template Principle\
\
This becomes one of the strongest architectural principles of the Citizen application.\
\
The Local Government page never changes.\
\
Only constitutional state changes.\
\
As the operating system evolves:\
\
Budgets appear.\
\
Projects appear.\
\
Procurement appears.\
\
Court judgments appear.\
\
Schools appear.\
\
Hospitals appear.\
\
The page itself remains stable.\
\
New constitutional objects simply project themselves into predefined regions.\
\
---\
\
# Long-Term Product Direction\
\
Version 1 intentionally limits itself to a small constitutional slice.\
\
The page demonstrates:\
\
\'95 Identity\
\
\'95 Relationships\
\
\'95 Budget\
\
\'95 Constitutional activity\
\
This is sufficient to establish the rendering model.\
\
Future constitutional domains will naturally plug into the same template.\
\
No redesign should be necessary.\
\
---\
\
# Relationship to CAOS\
\
The Citizen application should not expose CAOS.\
\
Citizens should experience:\
\
their Local Government\
\
their representatives\
\
their budget\
\
their constitutional record\
\
The operating system quietly guarantees that what they are seeing has been lawfully produced.\
\
CAOS should behave like electricity.\
\
Always present.\
\
Rarely seen.\
\
---\
\
# Constitutional Principle\
\
The Citizen application is not a government directory.\
\
It is not a news application.\
\
It is not social media.\
\
It is not Wikipedia.\
\
It is the constitutional profile of a Nigerian community.\
\
Every Local Government has one.\
\
Every citizen belongs to one.\
\
Every page is rendered from constitutional truth.\
\
Every page shares the same structure.\
\
Only the constitutional state projected into that structure changes over time.\
\
This principle is hereby frozen as the foundation of Citizen Application v1.\
